<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-24T18:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-24T18:36:00-05:00" n="1313" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1313">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Vera
                                    Cruz</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-24T17:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1912—5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>No foreigners hurt or property destroyed. City in the possession of
                            Federals. Díaz is a prisoner; if asylum is asked for will be
                            refused.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>